glosses.gloss: A cell that can be recharged

A rechargeable battery, storage battery, secondary cell, or accumulator is a type of electrical battery which can be charged, discharged into a load, and recharged many times, as opposed to a disposable or primary battery, which is supplied fully charged and discarded after use.
Type of electrical battery which can be charged, discharged into a load, and recharged many times; device that stores energy
A rechargeable battery.
A device that may be recharged.
이차 전지, 축전지는 외부의 전기 에너지를 화학 에너지의 형태로 바꾸어 저장해 두었다가 필요할 때에 전기를 만들어 내는 장치를 말한다.
An electrochemical cell is a device capable of either generating electrical energy from chemical reactions or facilitating chemical reactions through the introduction of electrical energy.
A device which produces electricity through chemical reactions, commonly referred to as a battery
Class of electrical power sources

The basic building block of a battery. It is an electrochemical device consisting of an anode and a cathode in a common electrolyte kept apart with a separator. This assembly may be used in its own container as a single cell battery or be combined and interconnected with other cells in a container to form a multicelled battery.
(computer science) a register that has a built-in adder that adds an input number to the contents of the register
In a computer's central processing unit, an accumulator is a register in which intermediate arithmetic and logic results are stored.
In a CPU, a processor register for storing intermediate results
A register in a calculator or computer used for holding the intermediate results of a computation or data transfer.
Computer science: register for holding intermediate results.
누산기 또는 어큐뮬레이터는 컴퓨터의 중앙 처리 장치에서 중간 산술 논리 장치 결과가 저장되는 레지스터이다.
A series of wagers in which the winnings from one wager are used as a stake for the subsequent wagers
A parlay, accumulator, or combo bet is a single bet that links together two or more individual wagers and is dependent on all of those wagers winning together.
A gambling term
A voltaic battery that stores electric charge

A rechargeable battery, storage battery, secondary cell, or accumulator is a type of electrical battery which can be charged, discharged into a load, and recharged many times, as opposed to a disposable or primary battery, which is supplied fully charged and discarded after use.
An accumulator is an energy storage device: a device which accepts energy, stores energy, and releases energy as needed.
An apparatus for storing energy or power
Type of electrical battery which can be charged, discharged into a load, and recharged many times; device that stores energy
A rechargeable device for storing electrical energy in the form of chemical energy, consisting of one or more separate secondary cells.
A wet-cell storage battery.
Wet-cell storage battery.

An accumulation of numeric data that can be used for reporting purposes, such as yearly taxable earnings for the T4 or W 2 statement, or used in a calculation. For example, Canada Pension Plan, Social Security, Medicare, and withholding taxes are based on accumulators. The contents of an accumulator can be manually adjusted, preset, and deleted.
